$$ {k_d} = {\left( {1 + \frac{d}{\alpha }} \right)^{{ - \gamma }}}, $$
\end{document}where d is the distance between two premises, and α and γ are two constant parameters. Long-range transmission was modeled by specifying a network of contacts between premises. Le Menach et al. (2006) chose a different approach, defining three values for the rate of transmission, each one being associated to a range of distances between two premises: short, medium, and long-range.
